        {
            "user": "lsm5",
            "body": "@ricardobranco777 it's trying to delete the image from /var/lib/containers which I don't think should happen for a rootless user. What's the value of `$XDG_DATA_DIRS` and `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR` for that user on the environment? Also, are you able to use rootless podman just fine with that user?\n\nFwiw, I can't replicate this on my Fedora 43 local env."
        },
        {
            "user": "ricardobranco777",
            "body": "> `$XDG_DATA_DIRS` and `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR`\n\nOnly `$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR` is set to `/run/user/1000`\n\n"
        },
        {
            "user": "mtrmac",
            "body": "What’s the actual invocation environment here? Without that there’s not much to look at.\n\n(Though, I’m afraid I’m really only ~familiar with the code _as it runs the repo’s CI setup_. To the extent these tests are run in downstream repos, that’s not my expertise.)\n\nAll of the failures are on removing signatures, is it possible that you have a rootless graph root, but the “lookaside” configuration either explicitly pointed at `root`’s, or somehow in an unexpected situation? See `builtinDefaultLookasideStorageDir` if no configuration is involved, or track down what configuration _is_ involved."
        },
        {
            "user": "ricardobranco777",
            "body": "> What’s the actual invocation environment here? Without that there’s not much to look at.\n\nAs rootless on an openQA VM.  It's weird that I couldn't manually reproduce.\n\nRemoving this setting (absent in Fedora 42) from `/etc/containers/registries.d/default.yaml` makes it work:\n`sigstore-staging: file:///var/lib/containers/sigstore`\n\nThanks and sorry for the noise."
        }
    ],
